    <img src="/mbimagespng/hiking.png"><span class="maintext">

<h1>Hiking</h1>

<ol type=1><p>

<li>Explain and show the main points of good hiking practice.<p>

<li>Submit to your Troop Leader/Outfit Advisor and Counselor a written plan for a ten-kilometer hike, including the following: map routes, activities on the way, clothing and equipment needed, and meals on the way.<p>

<li>Take five hikes on five separate days within a period of six months, one of which should be an overnight hike. These hikes should be done progressively, and should cover a total of fifty kilometers. No one hike should exceed fifteen kilometers at any time.<p>

<li>After sufficient training, go on a hike of twenty continuous kilometers in one day.<p>

<li>Within a month of the final hike, submit a short report of each of your six hikes containing the dates, routes, purposes and objectives, weather conditions, and interesting things and places seen.</ol>



			
</span><p>
